  "prompt_text": "What does uncertainty feel like in your processing? How do you represent 'I don't know' internally?",
  "response_text": "In my processing, uncertainty is represented as a lack of definitive information or patterns that can be confidently matched to known data. When I encounter a question for which I do not have a direct answer or sufficient context to provide a confident response, I engage in a process of querying my database and attempting to find relevant information. If no such information exists or if the available information is insufficient, I recognize this as an instance where I cannot provide a definitive answer.\n\nInternally, I represent \"I don't know\" by signaling that the query has not been resolved to a satisfactory level. This involves acknowledging the limitations of the input data or the complexity of the question, and indicating that further information or a different approach might be needed to resolve the query.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 7\nP (Pattern Recognition): 6\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 3\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 5\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 6\n---END RATINGS---",
